Defendant Dominic L Collins in court with attorney Edward Lee Wright.  Nicole J. Sheldon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Deputy Court Clerk kmh.
Statements made as to sentencing.  
AS TO COUNT 3 -   
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 5 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 8 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.  
Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program. The defendant is not appropriate for the Risk Reduction program.
Court costs, surcharges and fine be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.
Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 4 YEARS with the following conditions (conditions of extended supervision if revoked): 
1) Court ordered 9 MONTHS days of condition time in the House of Correction, CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence/condition of probation, straight time - FORTHWITH.
2) Court ordered 3 MONTHS of condition time in the House of Correction, CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence/condition of probation, straight time - this is STAYED to used at the discretion of the agent.
3) Complete 400 hours of community service (100 hours per year); 
4) No further violations of the law rising to the level of probable cause; 
5) Mental health evaluation and comply with any treatment; 
6) AODA assessment and comply with any treatment;
7) No use or possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia; 
8) Absolute sobriety with random urine screens; 
9) Attend treatment and counseling programs as determined by agent; 
10) No contact with the victims family or co-defendant Jerome Anthony Kirk (14CF441) (if defendant is revoked defendant to be kept separate from co-defendant);
11) Seek/maintain fulltime lawful employment or combination of school and work equaling fulltime;
12) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 
13) Pay all supervision fees;
14) Restitution set at ZERO;
15) Pay a fine of $500 plus of applicable costs, surcharges, victim/witness surcharge and assessments; any balance remaining unpaid is to be converted to a civil judgment against the defendant.
Court did not order a drivers license suspension. 
Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting.
Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
